.TH "t4vf_enable_pi" 9 "t4vf_enable_pi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4vf_enable_pi \- enable/disable a Port's virtual interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4vf_enable_pi
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "struct port_info *pi "  ","
.BI "bool rx_en "  ","
.BI "bool tx_en "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter
.IP "pi" 12
the Port Information structure
.IP "rx_en" 12
1=enable Rx, 0=disable Rx
.IP "tx_en" 12
1=enable Tx, 0=disable Tx

Enables/disables a Port's virtual interface.  If the Virtual
Interface enable/disable operation is successful, we notify the
OS-specific code of a potential Link Status change via the OS Contract
API \fBt4vf_os_link_changed\fP.
